Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Pakistan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification" was brought out in booklet by the Victorial Publishing House of Pakistan on Feb. 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work published on August 4, Juche 86 (1997) formulated the immortal exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung in the cause of national reunification and the three principles of national reunification, the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo and the 10-point programme for the great national unity as the three charters of national reunification. It clarified the tasks to accomplish the cause of national reunification based on them and the ways to do so.

Kim Jong Il's Birthday Celebrated Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- Meetings, film shows, photo exhibitions and art performances took place in Mexico, Tanzania, Egypt and Laos from Feb. 10 to 12 on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the events were photos showing the undying feats of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the film shows watched Korean films "The Great Leadership Guiding the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation to Victory" and "Old Home in Secret Camp in Mt. Paektu." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ramon Jimenez Lopez, president of the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism, referred to the originality and vitality of the Juche idea, Songun idea, highly praising the greatness and wise leadership of Kim Jong Il who has firmly defended the sovereignty of the country and dignity of the nation under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Francis F. Lyimo, chairman of the Tanzanian National Coordinating Committee of the Juche Idea Study Groups and vice-chairman of the Tanzania-DPRK Friendship Association, lauded the immortal exploits Kim Jong Il has performed by pursuing the unique Songun politics with the spirit and wisdom of Mt. Paektu and turning the DPRK into a bulwark of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at a meeting held in Tanzania.

Congratulations to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- The Bangladesh Institute of the Juche Idea extends warm congratulations to Kim Jong Il, the sun of the 21st century, upon receiving "International Kim Il Sung Prize" on his birthday. The institute said this in its statement on Feb. 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: Born in a revolutionary family, Kim Jong Il is a distinguished leader as he has performed undying feats on behalf of the times and humankind by successfully carrying forward the revolutionary cause of Juche started by President Kim Il Sung and wisely guiding the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the belief that the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il would victoriously lead the Korean people in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieve national reunification despite the imperialists' anti-DPRK moves and thus give a powerful impetus to the cause of global independence.

S. Korean Internet Homepages Observe February Holiday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- The south Korean progressive organizations reportedly posted special write-ups on their Internet homepages one after another on the occasion of Kim Jong Il's birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration posted on its Internet homepage photo-accompanied articles praising Kim Jong Il as a seasoned statesman, a distinguished strategist, extraordinary thinker and theoretician, incarnation of love for the people and the greatest leader in the present era guiding humankind along the most correct road. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage introduced a congratulatory letter sent to him by the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front on his birthday and his words calling for preserving the Juche character and national identity in the revolution and construction and on the Songun politics. It carried a poem "You represent an enduring motherland" written by Ri Jun Sik, Korean resident in Germany, in praise of him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification posted a fixed column titled "Special Write-up Dedicated to February 16" on its Internet homepage. Seen there were Kim Jong Il's work "The Songun Revolutionary Line Is a Great Revolutionary Line of Our Times and an Ever-Victorious Banner of Our Revolution" and several articles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions carried on its Internet homepage the instructions made by President Kim Il Sung on the greatness of Kim Jong Il and a joint congratulatory message sent to him on his birthday in the name of the Central Committee and Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea, the National Defence Commission, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and Cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils also posted articles highly praising Kim Jong Il on its Internet homepage.

Anti-GNP Wednesday Action Staged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) -- Members of the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration including its permanent joint representative Kwon O Chang and permanent adviser So Sang Ho reportedly staged a Wednesday action to denounce the Grand National Party of south Korea (GNP) on Feb. 21. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is shielding the military dictatorial regime instead of apologizing for its past crimes, they said, dismissing it as a rash act to revive the dictatorship even by turning back the wheel of history as a descendant of the regime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also accused the GNP of crying out for tightening the sanctions against the north, displeased with the peace process on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that the solidarity would continue to hold rallies and conduct information services every Wednesday to disclose and denounce the GNP's crimes.

Imperialists' Moves for "Globalization" under Fire  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 25 (KCNA) --The "globalization" much touted by the imperialists is nothing but a yoke of exploitation and plunder, domination and subjugation as it is intended to put other countries under their tight control and bleed the world people white to the maximum under the spurious signboard of "co-prosperity" and a neo- colonial system whereby to completely obliterate the Juche character and national identity of other countries and nations and turn the relations between the Western multi-national monopolies and the developing countries into those between the slave owner and slaves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists' moves for "globalization" involve various aspects of social life but it is mainly targeted on finance and trade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is one of the main goals of "globalization" to make breaches in different systems of national economies in many countries of the world through "liberalization" in the fields of finance and trade and make them spill over into other fields in a bid to convert the world economy into a uniform market economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reactionary nature of the "globalization" pushed forward by the imperialists is to completely stonewall the appearance of a new fair international economic order, bind the developing countries to a neo- colonial domination order and turn their politics into Western-style one through the "integration" of the world economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists' moves for "globalization" aimed at neo-colonizing the whole world are entailing evermore dangerous consequences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said "globalization" is driving society into chaos and triggering off evermore acute conflict and contradictions among different ethnic groups, religious sects and political forces. To make matters worse, this is leading to armed conflicts, causing bloodshed and making a great many people displaced. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "globalization" in the financial field is turning the world into a world in the grip of utter disorder where financial speculators ride roughshod. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "globalization" pushed forward by the imperialists is only widening the gap between the rich and the poor worldwide.

Congratulatory Visits Paid  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Figures of different circles in various countries paid congratulatory visits to the DPRK embassies in their capital cities on Feb. 15 and 16 on the occasion of Kim Jong Il's birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them were the third vice-premier of Uganda who is minister of Information and Nation Guidance and the senior advisor to its Presidency, the general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (United Marxist-Leninist), the general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist), the chairman of the Nepalese Association for Supporting Songun Politics, the director of the Gold Star Trade and Manpower Co. Ltd. of Vietnam, the chairman of the Ethiopian Youth Study Group of the Juche Idea and the general director of a tourist company of Malaysia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They laid floral baskets and bouquets before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and the full-length picture of them standing together before paying tribute to them.

Book "Great Banner of Victory" Published in Russia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- The Russian Union of Writers brought out the book "Great Banner of Victory" on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book carries his portrait and photos showing the feats performed by the peerlessly great persons. It contains songs created by Russian composer Sharin in high praises of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ceremony of releasing the book was held in Moscow on Feb. 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the union in a speech made at the ceremony lauded President Kim Il Sung, Kim Jong Il and Kim Jong Suk as the great persons recognized by the world. The DPRK is building socialism of its own style despite the pressure of the U.S. and other imperialists as it is led by Kim Jong Il, successor to the cause of the President, the chairman added.

Nigerian Group for Study of Songun Policy Formed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- The Nigerian Group for the Study of Songun Policy was inaugurated with due ceremony in Abuja on Feb. 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 M. M. Alhassan, chairman of the Nigerian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, said at the ceremony that he was pleased to see the inauguration of the study group on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il, the great leader of the Korean people and the world progressives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the necessity to uphold the Songun policy in order to defend global peace and security from the imperialists' evermore undisguised moves for aggression and war and successfully accomplish the human cause of independence, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the trend of the times to learn from the Songun policy, he stressed, calling on the group to make positive efforts for widely introducing the Songun idea and policy among the Nigerian people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the group was elected at the ceremony.

New Year's Day Celebrated in Uzbekistan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Koreans in Uzbekistan met in Tashkent City on Feb. 18 to celebrate the New Year's Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Sok Myong Son, chairman of the International United Confederation of Koreans, its officials, Korean residents and the DPRK ambassador to Uzbekistan and staff members of its embassy in Tashkent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting said that the conferment of "International Kim Il Sung Prize" upon Kim Jong Il on his birthday was an expression of high appreciation of the exploits he has performed by making immortal contributions to the noble cause for defending global peace and security and achieving independent progress of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called on all the Koreans in Uzbekistan to turn out in a vigorous drive to implement the tasks of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity under the uplifted banner of the June 15 joint declaration in the new year.

Floral Baskets Sent to DPRK Missions 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Political parties, institutions and organizations of different countries sent floral baskets to the DPRK missions from Feb. 12 to 16 on the occasion of Kim Jong Il's birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them were the Central Committee of the Revolutionary Socialist Party of India, the Defense Staff of Nigerian Armed Forces, the Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist), the British Coordinating Committee for Korean Friends, "Koryo Tour" Travel Agency in Britain, the Emperor Group and other different companies and unit of Hong Kong, China, and companies of Vietnam.

Reception Given by Secretary of Libyan People's Bureau
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Bashir Ramadan Khalifa Abu Janah, secretary of the People's Bureau of Libya to the DPRK, hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Feb. 23 to celebrate the birthday of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Choe Chang Sik, minister of Public Health, Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the C.C., the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Libyan secretary said in a speech at the reception that Kim Jong Il, who was born and grew up in Mt. Paektu, is always advancing the Korean revolution to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will, he stressed, develop the relations between Libya and the DPRK in different fields in conformity with the interests of the two peoples, true to the intentions of Colonel Moammer El Gaddafi and General Kim Jong Il, the great leaders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok in a speech said that the Korean people are rejoiced over the achievements made by the Libyan people in social and economic development and sincerely wish them greater success in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation would grow stronger in all fields by the joint efforts of the two countries.

United States Accused of Letting Loose War Outcries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- The U.S. secretary of Defense was lately reported to have cried out for getting the U.S. forces fully prepared to go into actions to cope with what he called someone's "threat." He blustered that the U.S. forces were having a series of war scenarios in the making in anticipation of the Korean war and a crisis to be created in the Pacific region and other contingencies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. military opened to the public the "PAC-3" newly deployed in its base in Okinawa, talking about "deterrence" to cope with somebody while the chairman of the U.S. Joint Chiefs of Staff prattled that disputes may break out in the Pacific region, on the Korean Peninsula, in particular. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed commentary carried in this regard observes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
These bellicose remarks clearly indicate the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is escalating its war exercises after deploying reinforcements of its forces on the Korean Peninsula and in its vicinity under the pretext of a "threat" from somebody. These moves only strip bare its aggressive and bellicose nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is foolish of the U.S. to try to gain something through "gunboat diplomacy" towards to the DPRK, as a sign of its show of power. It is the height of folly for the U.S. to attempt to browbeat the DPRK and test its will and strength through arms build-up and deployment of new type missiles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dialogue and military threat can never go together. The U.S. would be well advised to choose between dialogue and a military option. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is following with a high degree of vigilance the U.S. moves for a new war, concludes the commentary.

Extraordinary Meeting of Co-Chairmen of Pomminryon Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Co-chairmen of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminryon) had an extraordinary meeting Friday by way of exchanging facsimile messages among the north and the south and overseas sides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It discussed on the orientation of Pomminryon's actions for 2007. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report made there stressed the need for Pomminryon to discharge its mission and role in the struggle to carry out the tasks of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity this year and thus usher in a great heyday in realizing the cause of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It underlined the need to intensify the nationwide struggle against the U.S. on such occasions as the 25th anniversary of the arson on the American Cultural Service in Pusan, the 50th anniversary of the "UN Command", the 40th anniversary of the effectuation of the south Korea-U.S. "Status of Forces Agreement" and the fifth anniversary of the GIs' killing of Hyo Sun and Mi Son and thereby make this year witness the start of the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was stressed in the report that Pomminryon should give fresh momentum to the solidarity and alliance among the organizations for the reunification movement with the June 15 All-Korean Committee as an umbrella body and stage a dynamic mass movement for laying bare the true colors of the Grand National Party, a bulwark of conservatism, as an anti-reunification and treacherous party and glorifying the June 15 era through a great alliance against conservatism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A decision adopted at the meeting said Pomminryon will stir up an atmosphere of national reconciliation and unity and expand and develop the June 15 All-Korean Committee under the uplifted banner of the June 15 joint declaration and hold joint national events and reunification events of Koreans of all social standings on such important occasions as June 15 and August 15 and wage a powerful drive to celebrate June 15 as an anniversary common to the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The decision called for getting the "National Security Law" abolished, dynamically putting on a higher stage the struggle for making the South Headquarters of Pomminryon and the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification and the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils legal and the struggle for solidarity with mass organizations of the people from all walks of life and thus further enhancing the position of Pomminryon.

Message of Greetings to Emir of Kuwait
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Saturday sent a message of greetings to Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmed Al-Jaber Al-Sabah, Emir of Kuwait, on the occasion of the 46th national day and the 16th day of the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Believing that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to develop in the mutual interests in the future, too, the message wished the emir and the people of Kuwait greater success in their efforts for peace and prosperity of the country.

U.S. War Planes Busy with DPRK-Targeted Aerial War Exercises 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Flying corps of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces have recently started full-scale war exercises targeted against the DPRK after being transferred to their air force bases in south Korea from their overseas bases, according to military sources. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dozens of F-117 Stealth fighter bombers and formations of F-15 fighter bombers were busy with navigation drills and exercises of striking at ground targets in the sky above the areas of North and South Chungchong, Kyonggi and Kangwon provinces of south Korea on Feb. 23. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Feb. 21 E-3 conducted a drill of commanding the flying corps engaged in the exercises of striking at ground targets and navigation drills. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Feb. 15 and 16 F-117 Stealth fighter bombers staged night navigation and terrain familiarization drills. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the meantime, KC-135 was busy with in-flight refueling of war planes everyday as the war maneuvers of the newly deployed flying corps entered a full-scale phase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said madcap aerial war exercises staged by the U.S. imperialists in the wake of transfer of a wing of F-117 Stealth fighter bombers and its support personnel to their air force bases in south Korea from their mainland are dangerous military provocations to the DPRK and a clear expression of their intention to stifle it by force of arms.

Wreaths Laid before Bust of An Kil
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were placed before the bust of An Kil, a revolutionary martyr, at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery in Mt. Taesong Saturday to commemorate the centenary of his birth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen there was a wreath from General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Laid before the bust were wreaths in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, ministries, national institutions and educational organs and bunches of flowers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the wreath-laying ceremony paid a silent tribute to the memory of An Kil. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony were Kim Il Chol, Choe Yong Rim, Kim Ki Nam and others, servicepersons of the KPA and members of the bereaved family.

Letter to Japanese Diet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- The European Regional Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the Society for Cooperation among Koreans in Germany sent a joint letter to the Japanese Diet on Feb. 13 denouncing the Japanese government's unwarranted suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan which have become all the more undisguised recently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an unpardonable crime against humanity to brutally abuse the rights of Koreans in Japan and suppress them for the mere reason that they have different nationality and ideology, the letter pointed out, stressing that this act self-exposes before the world that Japan is a country of barbarians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter urged the Diet to properly discharge its duty and exercise its right at a time when the security authorities of Japan which styles itself a "law-governed state" are openly perpetrating the politically-motivated suppression of Chongryon over its just political, social, cultural and educational activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Japanese Diet, keeping mum about the unethical suppression of Koreans in Japan, continues to connive at and support it, we will solidarize with the world forces of justice and conscience and stage legitimate actions to denounce the Japanese government's suppression in front of the Japanese embassies in various parts of the world, the letter warned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed conviction that the progressive civil organizations and conscientious figures of Japan would launch actions in solidarity with Chongryon and Koreans in Japan in their struggle.

EE.UU. crea peligro de guerra, revela Rodong Sinmun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 24 de febrero (ATCC) -- Hace unos dias, el secretario de Defensa norteamericano dijo que a fin de hacer frente a la "amenaza" de alguien, sus tropas deben prepararse para ejecutar una guerra entera y anadio que estas elaboran varios guiones belicos suponiendo la guerra coreana o una crisis en la region del Pacifico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Al abogar por las "fuerzas contentivas" a alguien, la cupula militar norteamericana dio a la publicidad los misiles "Patriot" ubicados nuevamente en la base de sus tropas en Okinawa de Japon mientras el presidente de la Junta de los Jefes de Estado Mayor de EE.UU. habla tanto de un posible conflicto en la region del Pacifico, especialmente, en la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tales palabras belicosas reflejan evidentemente la politica hostil de EE.UU. a la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Asi revela el diario Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual de este sabado y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@EE.UU. intensifica los ejercicios belicos y ubica nuevas fuerzas armadas en la Peninsula Coreana  y sus periferias acusando a alguien, lo cual deviene una muestra contundente de la agresividad y belicosidad de este imperio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Es inutil el intento del imperio de sacar algun provecho practicando la "diplomacia de canonero" sobre la RPDC. Tambien resulta ridicula la intencion de amedrentar o probar la voluntad y las fuerzas de nuestro pais con el aumento armamentista y los misiles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Son incompatibles el dialogo y la amenaza militar. EE.UU. debe dejar en claro su posicion ante esta disyuntiva: el dialogo o la via militar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La RPDC observa con alta vigilancia las maniobras de provocacion de una nueva guerra de EE.UU.

Sesionada reunion de copresidentes de la APRP
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 24 de febrero (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar la vispera por facsimile entre el Norte, el Sur de Corea y ultramar la reunion de los copresidentes provisionales de la Alianza Pannacional por la Reunificacion de la Patria (APRP). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En la ocasion fue discutida la direccion de actividades de la APRP para 2007. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La APRP debe cumplir satisfactoriamente su mision y papel en la lucha por ejecutar las tres tareas de este ano: la preponderancia de la nacion, la defensa de la paz y el logro de la union para abrir una gran epoca de prosperidad en la realizacion de la causa de reunificacion independiente de la patria, comienza el informe presentado en el foro y subraya: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Hay que avivar mas las llamas de la lucha pannacional antiyanqui en varias ocasiones, tales como el 25 aniversario del incendio de la Casa Cultural de EE.UU. en Pusan, el 50 aniversario de la instalacion de la "comandancia de las fuerzas de las Naciones Unidas", el 40 aniversario de la entrada en vigor del "convenio de administracion" Sur de Corea - EE.UU. y el 5 aniversario del asesinato de Hyo Sun y Mi Son por parte de tropas norteamericanas, para  dar inicio, a cualquier precio, a la retirada de estas del suelo surcoreano. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La APRP debe ampliar en un nivel mas alto la solidaridad y la alianza de las entidades del movimiento por la reunificacion, originadas en el Comite Conjunto Nacional del 15 de Junio, y desplegar activamente el movimiento masivo por revelar la naturaleza anti-reunificacion y antinacional del "Gran Partido Nacional", bastion del conservadurismo, y glorificar la epoca del 15 de junio al formar una gran alianza contra las fuerzas conservadoras. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La resolucion aprobada en la reunion apunta que enarbolando la bandera de la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio, la APRP acentuara mas el clima de reconciliacion y unidad de la nacion, ampliara el Comite Conjunto Nacional del 15 de Junio a fin de organizar los actos conjuntos nacionales y los otros de distintos estratos para la reunificacion en el 15 de junio, el 15 de agosto y otras efemerides importantes y desarrollar con dinamismo el movimiento por fijar el 15 de junio como dia conmemorativo comun de la nacion coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Es preciso desplegar en un nivel mas alto la lucha por abolir la "ley de seguridad" y legalizar la direccion surena de la APRP y la Alianza Pannacional de Jovenes y Estudiantes por la Reunificacion de la Patria y la "Federacion de Consejos Generales de Estudiantes Universitarios del Sur de Corea" y las actividades solidarias con las organizaciones de masas de distintos sectores, de modo que la primera entidad afiance mas su posicion, puntualiza el documento.
